      "title": "Beacon HEX Generator",
      "body": '<h1 id="beacon_hex_generator">Beacon<em>HEX<&sol;em>Generator<&sol;h1><p>This script can generate a Beacon HEX command like:<&sol;p><blockquote><p>hcitool -i hci0 cmd 0x08 0x0008 1E 02 01 06 03 03 AA FE 16 16 AA FE 00 00 61 62 63 64<&sol;p><&sol;blockquote><p>And execute them in terminal to make our Raspberry Pi discoverable as Beacon.<&sol;p><h3 id="youcanusethisscriptin2ways">You can use this script in 2 ways:<&sol;h3><h4 id="1usingsetuppy">1. Using setup.py<&sol;h4><p>The easiest way to generate HEX code is to use setup.py script. This special script which generate command which execute iBeacon.py script with suitable args. <&sol;p><h4 id="2usingcommandargs">2. Using command args<&sol;h4><p>You can also execute iBeacon.py script directly. The args description is below:<&sol;p><h4 id="torunscriptyoumustsetupafewarguments">To run script You must set up a few arguments:<&sol;h4><ol><li>Type of message to generate, possible options are:<&sol;li><&sol;ol><ul><li>0: UUID + Major + Minor<&sol;li><li>1: URL<&sol;li><li>2: NameID + IstanceID<&sol;li><&sol;ul><ol><li><p>Arguments depends of first choice:<&sol;p><p>For 0: <br &sol;><img src="https:&sol;&sol;github.com&sol;radicalIT&sol;Beacon_HEX_Generator&sol;blob&sol;master&sol;imgs&sol;uid.png" alt="alt text" title="iBecaconUID" &sol;><&sol;p><blockquote><p>e.g. iBeacon.py 0 "63 6F 3F 8F 64 91 4B EE 95 F7 D8 CC 64 A8 63 B5" 3000 4567<&sol;p><&sol;blockquote><ul><li>UID <br &sol;><ul><li>16 Byte of two-HEX-character values  <&sol;li><li>e.g. "63 6F 3F 8F 64 91 4B EE 95 F7 D8 CC 64 A8 63 B5"<&sol;li><&sol;ul><&sol;li><li>Major value <br &sol;><ul><li>2 Byte value  <&sol;li><li>e.g. 3000  <&sol;li><&sol;ul><&sol;li><li>Minor value <br &sol;><ul><li>e.g. 4567  <&sol;li><&sol;ul><&sol;li><&sol;ul><p>For 1: <br &sol;><img src="https:&sol;&sol;github.com&sol;radicalIT&sol;Beacon_HEX_Generator&sol;blob&sol;master&sol;imgs&sol;url.png" alt="alt text" title="iBecaconUrl" &sol;><&sol;p><blockquote><p>e.g.    iBeacon.py 1 "facebook$me" 1 0  <&sol;p><&sol;blockquote><p>mean    https:&sol;&sol;www.facebook.com&sol;me<&sol;p><ul><li>Url <br &sol;><ul><li>Url address to display  <&sol;li><li>Max. 16 chars ( '$' is count as 1 char )  <&sol;li><li>Use $ to insert sufix  <&sol;li><li>e.g. 'facebook$me' with suffix 0 mean facebook.com&sol;me  <&sol;li><&sol;ul><&sol;li><li>Url prefix <br &sol;><ul><li>One of options: <br &sol;>0: http:&sol;&sol;www. <br &sol;>1: https:&sol;&sol;www. <br &sol;>2: http:&sol;&sol; <br &sol;>3: https:&sol;&sol;  <&sol;li><li>e.g. 3  <&sol;li><&sol;ul><&sol;li><li>Url suffix <br &sol;><ul><li>One of options: <br &sol;>0:    .com&sol; <br &sol;>1:    .org&sol; <br &sol;>2:    .edu&sol; <br &sol;>3:    .net&sol; <br &sol;>4:    .info&sol; <br &sol;>5:    .biz&sol; <br &sol;>6:    .gov&sol; <br &sol;>7:    .com <br &sol;>8:    .org <br &sol;>9:    .edu <br &sol;>10:    .net <br &sol;>11:    .info <br &sol;>12:    .biz <br &sol;>13:    .gov  <&sol;li><li>Is used in Url as $  <&sol;li><li>e.g. 0  <&sol;li><&sol;ul><&sol;li><&sol;ul><p>For 2: <br &sol;><img src="https:&sol;&sol;github.com&sol;radicalIT&sol;Beacon_HEX_Generator&sol;blob&sol;master&sol;imgs&sol;name.png" alt="alt text" title="iBecaconName" &sol;><&sol;p><blockquote><p>e.g. iBeacon.py 2 "11 22 33 44 55 66 77 88 99 00" "AA BB CC DD EE FF"<&sol;p><&sol;blockquote><ul><li>nameID <br &sol;><ul><li>10 Byte of two-HEX-character values<&sol;li><li>e.g. "11 22 33 44 55 66 77 88 99 00"<&sol;li><&sol;ul><&sol;li><li>istanceID <br &sol;><ul><li>6 Byte of two-HEX-character values<&sol;li><li>e.g. "AA BB CC DD EE FF"<&sol;li><&sol;ul><&sol;li><&sol;ul><&sol;li><&sol;ol>'
    },
